.TH greppy 1  "greppy 0.2.0" 
.SH NAME
greppy \- Sub\-millisecond local semantic code search for AI coding tools
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgreppy\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sub\-millisecond local semantic code search for AI coding tools
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
greppy\-start(1)
Start the greppy daemon
.TP
greppy\-stop(1)
Stop the greppy daemon
.TP
greppy\-status(1)
Show daemon status
.TP
greppy\-search(1)
Search for code in the current project
.TP
greppy\-index(1)
Index the current project
.TP
greppy\-list(1)
List indexed projects
.TP
greppy\-forget(1)
Remove a project from the index
.TP
greppy\-ping(1)
Ping the daemon (health check)
.TP
greppy\-auth(1)
Manage authentication for LLM features
.TP
greppy\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
Examples:
  greppy start              Start the background daemon
  greppy index              Index the current project
  greppy search "auth"      Search for \*(Aqauth\*(Aq in code
  greppy search \-l 5 "fn"   Get top 5 results for \*(Aqfn\*(Aq
  greppy search \-\-json "x"  Output results as JSON

For AI tools (Claude Code, Cursor, Aider):
  greppy search \-\-json "authenticate user" | head \-50
